PATCH: Two-part fix for syncPrices useEffect

FIX 1 — Add portfolioItemsRef to break the infinite loop
  Add after the existing `const safeSettings = ...` line:
  
  // Keep portfolioItems in a ref so syncPrices only re-fires when TILES change,
  // not when our own Firestore writes update portfolioItems
  const portfolioItemsRef = useRef(portfolioItems);
  useEffect(() => { portfolioItemsRef.current = portfolioItems; }, [portfolioItems]);

FIX 2 — Replace the syncPrices useEffect
  Change dependency array from [tiles, portfolioItems, updatePortfolioItem]
                              to [tiles, updatePortfolioItem]
  Use portfolioItemsRef.current instead of portfolioItems inside the effect
  In the hasChanges block: use portfolioItem.entryNetCredit (stored) — never recalculate it
